data.content:
## What Changed

Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi 10.0 upgraded to **OpenAPI.NET v2**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1. This is a major object-model rewrite:

| .NET 9 (OpenAPI.NET v1) | .NET 10 (OpenAPI.NET v2) |
|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any.OpenApiString` | Removed — use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonValue` |
| `schema.Example = new OpenApiString(…)` | `schema.Example = JsonValue.Create(…)` |
| `schema.Nullable = true/false` | `schema.Type` is now a `JsonSchemaType` flags enum; add/remove `JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "…" } }` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("…")` |

### Fixed code

```csharp
// ✅ Replace Microsoft.OpenApi.Any with System.Text.Json.Nodes
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // ✅ OpenApiString is gone — use JsonValue
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // ✅ Reference-wrapper types replace the Reference property pattern
    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                // ✅ Nullable property removed — clear the Null flag instead
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of each fix

1. **`using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any`** → `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` — the `Any` namespace no longer exists.
2. **`new OpenApiString("1.0")`** → `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` — all `IOpenApiAny` types are replaced by `JsonNode`.
3. **`new OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = … }`** → `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")` — v2 uses dedicated `*Reference` types instead of a `Reference` property.
4. **`property.Value.Nullable = false`** → `property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` — OpenAPI 3.1 expresses nullability via the `type` array, so `Nullable` was removed and `Type` became a flags enum.
